comments.body:
Yes, those settings can be added as new fields in S3Options. Given that the AWS SDK has lots of proxy options, perhaps it would be nice to put them in a nested struct, e.g.:
{code:c++}
struct {
  std::string scheme;
  std::string host;
  int port;
  std::string username;
  std::string password;
} proxy_options;
{code}
